physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Neck pain for 2 months; MRI showed an avidly enhancing, dural-based mass from C2 to C4 causing spinal cord compression; no neurological findings or cutaneous abnormality.
Lumbar puncture did not show any microfilariae in the CSF; ophthalmological examination was unremarkable.
Patient remained asymptomatic; showed no recurrence on imaging.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Improvement evidenced by the absence of symptoms and no recurrence.
